10 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Waiver request requirement -- definitions. (1) The department of
11 public health and human services shall submit to the food and nutrition service of the United States department
12 of agriculture a request for a waiver that seeks authorization to prohibit the use of supplemental nutrition
13 assistance program benefits for the purchase of candy and soft drinks.
14 (2) The waiver request must include:
15 (a) a justification citing public health concerns, the supplemental nutrition assistance program's
16 statutory intent, and cost savings to taxpayers;
17 (b) an implementation plan to ensure that existing point-of-sale systems used by Montana retailers
18 can properly enforce the restriction;
19 (c) a strategy for education and outreach to inform supplemental nutrition assistance program
20 recipients of alternative healthy food drink options; and
21 (d) a reporting mechanism to track the impact of the waiver, including spending patterns and
22 health outcomes.
23 (3) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
24 (a) "Candy" means a preparation of sugar, honey, or other natural or artificial sweeteners in
25 combination with chocolate, fruit, nuts, or other ingredients or flavorings in the form of bars, drops, or pieces
26 that does not require refrigeration.
